# Claude Code & Git AI Integration Guide

## Configuration Overview

Claude Code integrates with Git AI through native hook support. The system automatically installs necessary hooks when you install Git AI.

## Required Settings Configuration

The integration requires modifications to `~/.claude/settings.json` with the following structure:

```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "command": "git-ai checkpoint claude --hook-input stdin",
            "type": "command"
          }
        ],
        "matcher": "Write|Edit|MultiEdit"
      }
    ],
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "command": "git-ai checkpoint claude --hook-input stdin",
            "type": "command"
          }
        ],
        "matcher": "Write|Edit|MultiEdit"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Key Integration Points

**Supported Operations:** The hooks activate during Write, Edit, and MultiEdit operations, capturing "AI-code generated all the way to production."

**Hook Timing:** Both pre- and post-tool-use hooks execute the checkpoint command, ensuring comprehensive tracking.

## Setup Verification

After installation, verify proper integration by running:
```bash
git-ai status
```

You should observe multiple AI checkpoints linked to your current HEAD commit. If checkpoints don't appear, re-run `git-ai install-hooks` and restart all shell sessions and IDE instances.

